se.litsec.bankid.rpapi.types

Class Requirement

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.litsec.bankid.rpapi.types.Requirement

  • public class Requirement
extends Object
    Represents the structure in which a relying party can define how an authentication or signature process should be performed.

    Note: It is recommended to use the Requirement.RequirementBuilder to construct a Requirement.

    Author:
    Martin Lindström (martin.lindstrom@litsec.se)

      • setCardReader

        public void setCardReader(Requirement.CardReaderRequirement cardReader)
        Assigns the requirement for which type of smart card reader that is required.

        This condition should be combined with a certificatePolicies for a smart card to avoid undefined behavior.

        Parameters:
        cardReader - the card reader requirement

      • getCertificatePolicies

        Returns:

      • setCertificatePolicies

        public void setCertificatePolicies(List<String> certificatePolicies)
        Assigns the certificate policies telling which types of BankID:s that should be supported.

        It is recommended to use the Requirement.RequirementBuilder to set up certificate policies.

        Parameters:
        certificatePolicies - a list of certificate policy object identifiers

      • getIssuerCn

        public List<String> getIssuerCn()
        Returns the Nordea CA issuer common names. Controls which Nordea BankID types that are supported.
        Returns:
        a list of CN strings

      • setIssuerCn

        public void setIssuerCn(List<String> issuerCn)
        Assigns the Nordea CA issuer common names. Controls which Nordea BankID types that are supported.

        It is recommended to use the Requirement.RequirementBuilder to set up certificate policies and requirements for Nordea BankID usage.

        Parameters:
        issuerCn - a list of CN strings

      • getAutoStartTokenRequired

        public Boolean getAutoStartTokenRequired()
        Returns the autoStartTokenRequired flag that is used to determine whether the client must have been started using the autoStartToken.
        Returns:
        Boolean.TRUE or null (never FALSE)

      • setAutoStartTokenRequired

        public void setAutoStartTokenRequired(Boolean autoStartTokenRequired)
        Assigns the autoStartTokenRequired flag that is used to determine whether the client must have been started using the autoStartToken.

        A little bit of bad design is that its value can only be TRUE or not set at all. Therefore, if the supplied parameter is FALSE, the value will be un-set.

        Parameters:
        autoStartTokenRequired - the auto start flag

      • getAllowFingerprint

        public Boolean getAllowFingerprint()
        Returns the allowFingerprint flag telling whether finger print use should be allowed.

        For default setup null is returned. This means fingerprint is allowed for authentication and disallowed for signature.

        Returns:
        the allowFingerprint flag or null for default behaviuor

      • setAllowFingerprint

        public void setAllowFingerprint(Boolean allowFingerprint)
        Assigns the allowFingerprint flag telling whether finger print use should be allowed.

        For default behaviour, this method need to be invoked.

        Parameters:
        allowFingerprint - the allowFingerprint flag
